,`.shift` cut only one item from the begining of the array, to use it you need a loop to cut as many as you want! Using `.splice(0, amount)` will cut `amount` of items from the begining so no loop is needed! **If you'll need to loop through the result array of the `splice`ing** then use `shift` . **If you'll use the return array as a whole** then use `.splice`. One thing to mention is that `splice` is safer because(`[1, 2].splice(0, 10000) === [1, 2]`), in `shift` version you'll have to check if there still element in the array to see if you'll continue or not(otherwise undefineds ar returned)!","Embed Field: ""Operation passed in cannot be an array"" compass error - but JSON isn't an array
